name: methylenetetrahydrofolate dehydrogenase (NADP+)
classes: Acting on the CH-NH group of donors;
With NAD+ or NADP+ as acceptor
comment: In eukaryotes, occurs as a trifunctional enzyme also having methenyltetrahydrofolate cyclohydrolase (EC 3.5.4.9) and formate---tetrahydrofolate ligase (EC 6.3.4.3) activity. In some prokaryotes occurs as a bifunctional enzyme also having methenyltetrahydrofolate cyclohydrolase activity (EC 3.5.4.9).

orthologs.K00288: methylenetetrahydrofolate dehydrogenase (NADP+) / methenyltetrahydrofolate cyclohydrolase / formyltetrahydrofolate synthetase
